{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013KgSyrMqrtAmwXBPuCP9Lp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QBoTYuL6GrPgBLUTKieYXy","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Garlic Broccoli.generated.22.txt","content":"PREVIOUS PAGE CONTENT - RECIPE FRAGMENT\nPreheat oven to 325°F and prepare a rimmed sheet pan.\nIn a large bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients: 2 cups all-\npurpose flour, ½ teaspoon of salt, and ¼ teaspoon ground pepper. The\nmixture should resemble coarse breadcrumbs when ready. Fold in ¾ cup\nchopped nuts gently to avoid crushing them. Pour this nto a loured work\ncounter and knead for approximately 3-5 minutes until smooth.\nRoll out dough to ¼-inch thickness using a wooden rolling pin.\nCut into ⅜-inch squares and place on prepared baking sheet.\nBake at 225°C/435-VI0°F for 18-22 minutes until golden brown.\nCool completely before serving with buttercream frosting.\nGARBLED TEXT UuIw fghVx kknmO pqrSt\n====================================================================\n\nROASTED GARLIC BROCCOLI\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n• 1½ pounds fresh broccoli florets\n• 6 cloves garlic, minced\n• ¼ cup extra virgin olive oil\n• 1 teaspoon sea salt\n• ½ teaspoon black pepper\n• ½ teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional)\n• Zest of 1 lemon\n• 2 tablespoons fresh parmesan cheese\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F). Line a large baking sheet with\nparchment paper for easy cleanup.\n\n2. In a large bowl, toss the broccoli florets with the minced garlic.\nDrizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and black pepper. Mix\nuntil all pieces are evenly coated.\n\n3. Spread the broccoli in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet.\nRoast for 20-25 minutes until the florets are tender and the tips are\nslightly charred.\n\n4. Remove from the oven and immediately sprinkle with red pepper flakes\nif desired. Add lemon zest and fresh parmesan cheese while still hot.\n\n5. Serve immediately as a side dish or main course component.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":94776,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":94776},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ce049df-e6ec-43f0-8acf-b8060ae53121","uuid":"3f1a2e7f-0adb-4a13-84d1-5c3d8fae8915"}
