{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DAeUYXBCv94hn9bk2NsxSs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019TdQBrp81KvBbjPnvfXfQu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beet and Goat Cheese Salad.generated.22.txt","content":"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW:\n[Page 47 - Recipe Continuation]\n...and fold in the remaining walnuts. The batter should be thick enough\nto hold its shape but still pourable. Add ½ cup plus ı tablespoon of\nbuttermilk if too thick. Pour into prepped loaf pan and bake at 160°C\nfor 45-50 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.\n\nCool in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack. The\ncrust should be golden-brown and crispy when properly baked. Some\nrecipes call for a dusting of powdered sugar or a glaze of melted white\nchocolate mixed with coconut oil.\n\nThe texture should be moist throughout, not dry or crumbly. This is often\na sign that too much flour was incorporated or baking time was excessive.\n\nRemove any excess crumbs from the coun-ter and wash your hands before\nbeginning the next preparation. Make sure all equipment is clean before\nproceeding to avoid cross-contamination of flavors.\n\nCORRUPTED SECTION: jkQpMn vhtyWz XfGhJ pQrStU vWxYzA bCdEfG\nPage 48\n====================================================================\n\nBEET AND GOAT CHEESE SALAD\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n• 4 medium red beets, roasted and peeled\n• 150g fresh goat cheese, crumbled\n• 4 cups mixed salad greens (arugula, spinach, romaine)\n• ¼ cup toasted walnuts, roughly chopped\n• ¼ cup balsamic vinaigrette\n• Salt and pepper to taste\n• Optional: fresh mint leaves\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Roast beets at 190°C for 45-60 minutes until tender. Peel when cool\nand cut into wedges.\n\n2. Arrange salad greens on individual plates or a large platter.\n\n3. Top with beet wedges and scatter crumbled goat cheese over the greens.\n\n4. Sprinkle toasted walnuts over the salad.\n\n5. Drizzle with balsamic vinaigrette just before serving.\n\n6. Garnish with fresh mint if desired. Season with salt and pepper.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTION: Serves 4 as a side or 2 as a light main course.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":96090,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":602},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ce049df-e6ec-43f0-8acf-b8060ae53121","uuid":"4b43a242-7432-459a-8059-ea0f3cedbb8e"}
