{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018nasPKZgimqXC77JHvUpy6","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Chocolate Chip Cookies.generated.22.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ce049df-e6ec-43f0-8acf-b8060ae53121","uuid":"b3909610-0bf9-430a-9ae4-fa40efcbc672","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Chocolate Chip Cookies.generated.22.txt","content":"Page 23 - DESSERTS & BAKED GOODS\n\nCHOCOLATE CHIP COOKIES\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n• 2¼ cups all-purpose flour\n• 1 teaspoon baking soda\n• 1 teaspoon salt\n• 1 cup (225g) butter, softened\n• ¾ cup granulated sugar\n• ¾ cup brown sugar\n• 2 large eggs\n• 2 teaspoons vanilla extract\n• 2 cups chocolate chips\n\nMETHOD:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 190°C (375°F). Grease baking sheets or line with\nparchment paper.\n\n2. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.\n\n3. In a large bowl, cream together butter and both sugars until fluffy.\nBeat in eggs and vanilla extract.\n\n4. Gradually blend in the flour mixture.\n\n5. Stir in chocolate chips.\n\n6. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto prepared sheets.\n\n7. Bake 9-11 minutes until golden brown.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
