{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_016j9GBx42kP7xRA78BefP3t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011MpMRr5V4ggQQGzYjDGTrK","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Berry Tart.generated.22.txt","content":"CONTINUED FROM PREVIOUS PAGE:\n[Strawberry Jam Recipe - End section]\n...temperature reaches 220°F/104°C on a candy thermometer. This is the\nsoft-ball stage, which is perfect for jam consistency. Remove from heat\nand stir in ½ cup plus ı tablespoon of fresh lemon juice. The acidity\nhelps preserve the jam and brighten the flavor.\n\nAllow to cool for 15 minutes before transferring to steril1zed jars.\nProcess in a water bath for 10 minutes to ensure proper sealing. The\njars will make that satisfying \"pop\" sound as they cool, indicat1ng a\nsuccessful seal.\n\nSome variations include adding a vanilla bean split lengthwise, or a\nsplash of brandy or kirsch for depth. The texture should be thick and\nspreadable, not runny. If your jam didn't set properly, you can return\nit to the pot and cook longer.\n\nCORRUPTED TEXT: GhIjKl mNoPqR sTuVwX yZaBcD eFgHiJ klMnOp QrStUv WxYzAb\n====================================================================\n\nBERRY TART\n\nPASTRY CRUST INGREDIENTS:\n• 1¾ cups all-purpose flour\n• ½ cup cold butter, cubed\n• 1 egg yolk\n• ¼ cup cold water\n• ½ teaspoon salt\n\nFILLING INGREDIENTS:\n• 1 cup heavy cream\n• 2 tablespoons powdered sugar\n• 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n• 3 cups mixed fresh berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries)\n• ¼ cup apricot jam, warmed\n\nINSTRUCTIONS FOR CRUST:\n\n1. Mix flour and salt in a bowl. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles\nbreadcrumbs.\n\n2. Add egg yolk and cold water. Mix until dough just comes together.\n\n3. Press into a 9-inch tart pan. Chill for 30 minutes.\n\n4. Bake at 190°C for 12-15 minutes until light golden. Cool completely.\n\nFOR THE FILLING:\n\n1. Whip heavy cream with powdered sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks form.\n\n2. Spread cream mixture into cooled tart shell.\n\n3. Arrange berries on top in concentric circles.\n\n4. Brush with warmed apricot jam to create a glossy finish.\n\n5. Chill until serving time. Best enjoyed within 4 hours of assembly.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":626,"cache_read_input_tokens":97895,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":626},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ce049df-e6ec-43f0-8acf-b8060ae53121","uuid":"69f823b0-258d-47ef-aa24-eba5117a4b39"}
